In article <1994Feb6.122512.16863@umiami.ir.miami.edu> mfroomki@umiami.ir.miami.edu (Michael Froomkin) writes:
      1) If I have Clipper, is there any technical obstacle to using software
   encryption as well?
Assuming you can send data across your CLipper system (either a data
modem interface or your own modem sending the audio to the clipper),
you can do both at once, but you could have just done the real
encryption without the clipper.

      2) If I use Clipper + software crypto, am I any less secure than if I use
   the same software crypto alone?

Technically, no, except for traffic analysis, since they can find out
the Clipper serial number for both phones.
On the other hand, it may attract government attention,
either for decryption (if you use a wimpy encryption inside Clipper),
or electronic or other eavesdropping.
